{
  "texts": [
    "To mitigate these problems, researchers need to develop robust calibration techniques along with standardized data collection protocols.",
    "For example, integrating environmental sensors with olfactory devices can provide real-time contextual data, enabling automatic corrections for variations and ensuring consistent performance in diverse conditions.",
    "Secondly, current sensor technologies struggle with inherent limitations in selectivity and sensitivity.",
    "Electronic noses (e-noses) often find it difficult to distinguish between structurally similar odor molecules, such as isomers, due to limited receptor designs and overlapping responses (Gutiérrez and Horrillo 2014).",
    "Recent advancements in materials science, especially through the utilization of nanomaterials, have the potential to significantly enhance sensor sensitivity and odor differentiation."
  ]
}